# Terraform Multi-Cloud Lab

This project demonstrates a reusable Infrastructure as Code approach for provisioning and managing cloud resources across multiple environments using Terraform. It is designed as a portfolio lab to showcase modular Terraform patterns, environment separation, state management concepts, and deployment automation practices relevant to DevOps and cloud engineering roles.

## Project Goals
- Build reusable Terraform modules
- Organize infrastructure by environment
- Demonstrate scalable IaC structure
- Show cloud provisioning workflow and best practices

## Tools Used
Terraform, AWS, Azure, Git, YAML
